<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="389" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,374,688]" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">
Among all the material examined to revise the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1864" box="[757,874,375,400]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Monastria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[757,874,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Monastria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the 
<typeStatus box="[975,1023,375,401]" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunberg, 1826" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1826" box="[1062,1432,374,400]" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Blatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis box="[1062,1242,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Blatta papillosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thunberg, C. P." box="[1250,1432,374,400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" pagination="1 - 276" refId="ref17323" refString="Thunberg, C. P. (1826) Blattarum novae species descriptae. Meimoires de l'Acadeimie impeiriale des sciences de St. Peitersbourg, 10, 1 - 276." type="journal article" year="1826">Thunberg, 1826</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1864" box="[494,611,411,436]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Monastria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,611,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Monastria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
very early and maintained until today after being synonymized several times. As can be seen in the Fig. 18, the coloration, pronotum, head, tegmina and general shape of this specimen does not correspond to those that characterize the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1864" box="[772,889,483,508]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Monastria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[772,889,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Monastria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the general characteristics of this species are in accordance with the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1937" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1937" box="[519,796,518,544]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Hiereoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[519,661,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Hiereoblatta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[667,796,518,544]" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" pagination="207 - 258" refId="ref16871" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1937) New or little known Neotropical Blattidae (Orthoptera). Number four. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 63, 207 - 258." type="journal article" year="1937">Rehn, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 1D) as described in our identification key. Here, for the sake of delimiting the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1864" box="[555,672,555,580]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Monastria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[555,672,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Monastria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we propose the new combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tarli &amp; Grandcolas &amp; Pellens" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1055,1308,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Hiereoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis box="[1055,1308,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Hiereoblatta papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We do not propose here to solve the synonyms of this species because, as was the case for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1864" box="[1049,1166,591,616]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Monastria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1049,1166,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Monastria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1937" box="[1294,1436,590,616]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Hiereoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1294,1436,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="389">Hiereoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
needs to be revised, and any proposition of solution of the several synonymies would be premature without a careful study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
